content:
This module provides a robust way to initialize and access the Firebase Admin SDK for backend operations within the DocMed application.

It handles the secure loading of Firebase credentials from environment variables and ensures that the Firebase app and Firestore database instances are initialized only once.

## Key Exports

*   `getAdminApp()`: Initializes and returns the Firebase Admin `App` instance. It checks if an app is already initialized and returns it, otherwise it initializes a new one using credentials from environment variables (`FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`, `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL`, `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY`).
*   `getAdminDb()`: Returns the initialized Firestore database instance. It ensures the Firestore instance is created only once by leveraging the `getAdminApp()` function.

## Usage

To interact with Firestore from your backend code, you can import and use `getAdminDb()`:

```typescript
import { getAdminDb } from '../lib/firebase-admin';

async function getUserData(userId: string) {
  const db = getAdminDb();
  const userDoc = await db.collection('users').doc(userId).get();

  if (!userDoc.exists) {
    console.log('No such document!');
    return null;
  } else {
    return userDoc.data();
  }
}
```

## Environment Variables

This module relies on the following environment variables for Firebase authentication:

*   `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`: Your Firebase project ID.
*   `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL`: The client email associated with your Firebase service account.
*   `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY`: The private key of your Firebase service account. Ensure that any newline characters in the key are properly escaped (e.g., `\n`).

If these variables are not set, an error will be thrown during initialization.
